• 1 point for letting M be (x,y) and forming vectors CM = (x, y-4) and MP = (2-x, 2-y);
• 1 point for setting up and explicitly expanding the dot product condition CM · MP = 0;
• 1 point for correctly simplifying each step clearly to maintain clarity;
• 1 point for obtaining the correct final locus equation: (x-1)²+(y-3)² = 2.

• 1 point for identifying that |OP| = |OM| implies O is on the perpendicular bisector of PM, detailing perpendicular bisector properties;
• 1 point for correctly deducing the slope of ON, confirming the negative reciprocal relation for PM;
• 1 point for writing the correct line equation with thorough justification using point-slope form.

• 1 point for clearly computing the required distances (e.g., from O to the line and chord length using circle properties);
• 1 point for explicating the relationship and intermediate steps to find the length of PM, verifying intermediate results;
• 1 point for substituting these values into the triangle area formula to arrive at the correct area, 16/5, explaining each substitution.

